      </p>

      <!-- Billing Section - Critical -->
      <h2>Billing and Payment</h2>

      <h3>How Billing Works</h3>
      <p>
        mbuzz uses a <strong>prepaid base plan with metered overage</strong> model:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Base plan</strong>: You pay your monthly plan fee in advance at the start of each billing cycle</li>
        <li><strong>Included records</strong>: Your plan includes a set number of records per month (e.g., 1M for Starter). Records include visitors, sessions, events, and conversions</li>
        <li><strong>Overage</strong>: If you exceed your limit, we automatically charge your card for additional blocks (size varies by plan)</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Overage Charges</h3>
      <p>
        When you exceed your plan's record limit:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>We charge your card <strong>immediately</strong> for one block at your plan's overage rate</li>
        <li>Charges are in full blocks (no partial blocks)</li>
        <li>Each additional block of records triggers another charge</li>
        <li>You can track your usage in real-time on the dashboard</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Current overage rates:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Starter: $5 per 250K records</li>
        <li>Growth: $15 per 1M records</li>
        <li>Pro: $50 per 5M records</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We send email notifications at 80% and 100% of your plan limit, and for each overage charge.
      </p>

      <h3>Free Tier</h3>
      <p>
        The Free tier includes up to <%= free_event_limit_full %> records per month. This is a <strong>hard cap</strong>:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>When you reach <%= free_event_limit_display %> records, we stop storing new records</li>
        <li>There are no overage charges on the Free tier (no payment method required)</li>
        <li>To continue tracking beyond <%= free_event_limit_display %>, you must upgrade to a paid plan</li>
        <li>Your record counter resets at the start of each monthly cycle</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Payment Failures</h3>
      <p>
        If a payment fails (overage charge or plan renewal):
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Immediately</strong>: We stop storing new records</li>
        <li>Your existing data remains accessible (read-only)</li>
        <li>We retry the payment: after 24 hours, 72 hours, and 7 days</li>
        <li>We send email notifications for each retry attempt</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Important</strong>: Records that occur during a payment failure are <strong>not stored</strong>
        and <strong>cannot be recovered</strong>. Once payment succeeds, record storage resumes, but lost
        records are gone permanently.
      </p>
      <p>
        For plan renewals, we provide a 3-day grace period where records continue to be stored while
        we retry the payment.
      </p>

      <h3>Plan Changes</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Upgrades</strong>: Take effect immediately. You receive prorated credit for your current plan</li>
        <li><strong>Downgrades</strong>: Take effect at the start of your next billing cycle</li>
        <li><strong>Cancellation</strong>: Your plan remains active until the end of the current billing cycle. No prorated refunds</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Refunds</h3>
      <p>
        We don't offer refunds for partial months or unused records. If you believe you were incorrectly
        charged, <%= link_to "contact us", contact_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500" %>.
      </p>

